body:
python post commit failed because it executed using master branch code: https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-3120

java pre-commit failed because it executed on the bad worker (beam8). There are no java related changes here.

I think this is ready to merge. Could you PTAL?
python tests failed after executing on beam8. Was not that worker blacklisted? (cc: @kennknowles)
Maven was killed with exit code 137 while running example ITs in direct runner, and there was an ApexRunner failure according to the summary; neither of those seems likely to be related to this.
@chamikaramj, how many attempts should we attempt ;-)
Ok, I give up. Will test locally and commit :)
Jenkins beefed again and appears to be rebooting.
Will take a look in the next day or two, thanks for the reminder.

I went in and did it manually, not through modifying all of our Groovy scripts. So the seed job will revert it. But it seems too odd to commit `&& !beam8` to the repo. We could, though. I didn't get a chance to chat w/ infra about it today.
@jbonofre build now seems to be green
@jbonofre build passed if you have a minute
Cool. Thanks. I'm back from vacation tomorrow, I will take a look then.

R: @charlesccychen (for an overall review including DirectRunner specific logic)
R: @jkff (for SDF machinery)

cc: @robertwb

R: @XuMingmin @xumingming
Could you please take a look?
What's the status of this PR?

Run Java Precommit.
@chamikaramj, please merge this if there isn't much chance that jenkins would pass.
Tests are still failing, any idea why?
Note to committers : please close this as duplicate of #3969
If we're not going to finish this soon, let's close the PR. We can always reopen the PR later.
I pinged https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/INFRA-14819. This PR needs to have kubectl installed in Beam Jenkins executors and currently only executor beam1 has it.
Please associate a JIRA issue with this as well.
@markflyhigh is this ready to be merged now?
Jenkins issues. I'll try to locally test and merge.
R: @peihe any status on this PR?
@robertwb have you had a chance to look at this?
Looks like tests are failing and this needs to be rebased.
@kennknowles have you had a chance to look at this again?
I need to make some progress on it before it is appropriate for a reviewer. I'll close it for now.
Is this for the cases where groovy files picks up python and pip from different installations? Can we fix it at the source?
Thanks! Looks reasonable, but I'll hand over further review to @aljoscha .
All looked good, so I fixed up the findbugs warning and merged. Thanks!
Do we need to update the parameters in https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/239319b2a093cdb5c63375eddb5a91ac70172641/sdks/python/apache_beam/io/gcp/datastore/v1/datastoreio.py#L335 ?

build failure was a timeout.  rebasing.

LGTM, I fixed some whitespace and simplified the test to just use Object since it meets the criteria that we need.

I don't think we need to update datastoreio module. project==dataset currently and we are consistent across Java and Python. This change simply allows this example to be used for cases where project where the job is executed is different from the project where the dataset is stored.

The change LGTM.

Do we at least want to document that project argument can take a dataset? Or is it obvious for Datastore users that these two things are interchangeable?
Thanks. Updated the datastoreio documentation to clarify that the project is the project to read from/write to.
Our machines/backing channels seem to keep disconnecting from Jenkins
Gonna cancel the other builds to save Jenkins hours.
I haven't had a chance - sorry for the delay!

Wanted to clarify: I'm planning to merge this as-is (with the minor doc fixups), just haven't gotten around to it yet, and I was suggesting that afterwards maybe you could drive the discussion about replacing the stock ApproximateUnique transform with this.

CC: @iemejia

@zangshayang1 I see some tests failed in the jenkins job, can you take a look?
https://builds.apache.org/job/beam_PreCommit_Java_MavenInstall/15409/org.apache.beam$beam-sdks-java-extensions-sql/
